Veteran actor Kanayo O. Kanayo has urged the public to treat with levity claims on ‘sex for roles’ in Nollywood. From time to time there have been allegations bordering on s3x for roles, a case where senior colleagues in the movie industry demand s3xual relation from upcoming acts to offer them roles in movies. In a recent Instagram post, the thespian shared a video where he’s seen directing on a movie set.   Nigerian Idol 7: Winner to get N100m as Binance, Bigi join…     Jaruma remanded after Regina Daniel’s husband petition     I suck at showing interest in people – Ex-BBNaija’s…   Captioning the post, KOK said many girls cry wolf and fabricate the ‘sex for roles’ tale because they are unable to deliver the roles they are assigned, which he termed ‘shameful. - Advertisement - “When you hear of s3x for roles in Nollywood, please do not believe all you are told. “Many of the girls are not working hard to live up to the roles they are cast for. Quite a shame.”